    "Climate change is widely expected to have a significant impact on economic activity for a whole host of countries around the world.",
    "1 In his Nobel Prize Lecture, Nordhaus (2019) summed up the consensus on climate change: global warming is a threat to humankind and the natural world.",
    "The economic implications of climate change are potentially huge for firms, households and government policy.",
